To find the range of the function, we first need to determine the critical points.
\begin{align*}p(x) &= \frac{x^2 + x + 1}{x^2 + 1}\\p’(x) &= \frac{(2x + 1)(x^2 + 1) – (x^2 + x + 1)(2x)}{(x^2 + 1)^2}\\ &= \frac{(2x^3 + 2x + x^2 + 1) – (2x^3 + 2x^2 + x)}{(x^2 + 1)^2}\\&= \frac{-x^2 + 1}{(x^2 + 1)^2}\end{align*}

The critical points are at <math>\type{math.t} x = +1 </math> and <math>\type{math.t} x = -1 </math>. By testing values before <math>\type{math.t} x = -1 </math>, we find that the range of the function is <math>\type{math.t} range p(x) = [0.5,1] </math>.</think> <answer>range p(x) = [0.5,1]</answer>

